article.headline: Morgan State 67, MD Eastern Shore 60
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Joseph McLean scored 17 points to lead three Morgan State players in double figures, and the Bears overcame a slow start to beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 67-60 on Saturday. Demetrius Branch had 13 points, and Clinton Cunningham had 10 for Morgan State (4-22, 4-11 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Senior Tim Parham had a career-high 29 points and a season-high 18 rebounds for the Hawks (5-20, 2-13), who were done in by poor shooting -- 37 percent from the field and 11-for-27 (40.7 percent) from the free-throw line. Maryland-Eastern Shore opened the game with a 15-4 run and led 27-26 at halftime. The Hawks tied the score five times in the second half, the last time with 11:32 remaining, but never took another lead. McLean's jumper with 5:59 left capped a 15-4 run by Morgan State and gave the Bears an 11-point lead, their largest of the game.
